yongheng added on 2020-03-03 19:04:08:
Consider the following POC:
---
CREATE TABLE v0(v1);
INSERT INTO v0 VALUES(0.100000);
CREATE VIRTUAL TABLE v2 USING fts4(v5, v3);
CREATE TRIGGER BEFORE INSERT ON v0 BEGIN DELETE FROM v0
WHERE(SELECT v2 FROM v2 ORDER BY v5);
END;
INSERT INTO v2(v3) VALUES(1.100000);
INSERT INTO v0 VALUES(0), (10.100000)
---

It triggers an assertion in debug build of trunk
drh added on 2020-03-03 20:49:32:
For debug and testing builds, SQLite adds logic that attempts to locate cases
where a virtual-machine register is used when it is uninitialized.  This ticket
found a false-positive in that uninitialized-register detection logic.
No impact on release builds.
